R Markdown

This is an R Markdown document. Markdown is a simple formatting syntax for authoring HTML, PDF, and MS Word documents. For more details on using R Markdown see http://rmarkdown.rstudio.com.

When you click the Knit button a document will be generated that includes both content as well as the output of any embedded R code chunks within the document. You can embed an R code chunk like this:

summary(cars)
##      speed           dist       
##  Min.   : 4.0   Min.   :  2.00  
##  1st Qu.:12.0   1st Qu.: 26.00  
##  Median :15.0   Median : 36.00  
##  Mean   :15.4   Mean   : 42.98  
##  3rd Qu.:19.0   3rd Qu.: 56.00  
##  Max.   :25.0   Max.   :120.00

Including Plots

You can also embed plots, for example:

Note that the echo = FALSE parameter was added to the code chunk to prevent printing of the R code that generated the plot.

question 1: Yes, it says it skews right and you can see the outliers in the boxplot.

question 2: Pick 5 variables ad describe the distribution

First Variable: Crim = per capita crim rate by town - the distribution is skewd right meaning that most of the towns dont experience that much crime.

Second Variable: Age= the proportion of owener occupied units. - the distribution is skewd to the left, meaning that the majority of housing is owner occupied.

Third Variable: rm= average number of rooms per dwelling - the distribution is normal, it seems as though the avergae number of rooms per dwellng is between 5-8 rooms

Fourth Variable: tax= full value property-tax rate - distribution is skewd to the left

Fith Variable: lstat
